		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Make sure the book on assembly you got deals with processors like the 6502. If it deals with Intel chips or the Z80, it'll just make it 10x harder than what it is on the NES and it won't help you learn how to do 6502 as well either.<br /><br />My advice? Nerdy Nights on Nintendoage. Google it, you'll find it. Obelisk 6502 (google that to find the site) has a good 6502 reference and instruction overview too. And addressing mode explanations. And everything you'd need help with.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
